<p class="p">By contrast, if we know only the future occurrence probability of the scenario s, i.e., 
 <italic class="italic">P</italic>(
 <italic class="italic">s</italic>), and the decision can be given only once at 
 <italic class="italic">t</italic> = 0, we must explore the optimal pathway 
 <bold class="bold">x</bold>(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>) considering all future possible scenarios. In this case, control variables 
 <bold class="bold">x</bold>(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>) should be identical across the future scenarios as shown in the case (b) of Fig. 
 <xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig" class="xref">2</xref>. When we maximize the expected objective function, the optimal pathway 
 <bold class="bold">x</bold>
 <sup class="sup">***</sup>(
 <italic class="italic">t</italic>) is obtained by solving
 <disp-formula id="Equ2" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">2</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M3" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\mathop {\hbox{max} }\limits_{{{\mathbf{x}}(t)}} .\quad \sum\nolimits_{{\,s}} {P(s)f({\mathbf{x}}(t)|{\mathbf{a}}(s))} .$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M4" display="block" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <munder class="munder">
      <mtext class="mtext">max</mtext>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi mathvariant="bold" class="mi">x</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi class="mi">t</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </munder>
     <mo class="mo">.</mo>
     <mspace width="1em" class="mspace"/>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
       <mi class="mi">s</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">P</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      <mi class="mi">f</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="bold" class="mi">x</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">t</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">|</mo>
      <mi mathvariant="bold" class="mi">a</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mo class="mo">.</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
